basically, i need something i can build in the bahamas (so not expensive and fairly simple) that will allow me to collect sediment cores during a scuba dive. Also, theoretically, i would like to take multiple sediment cores per dive, so i need some sort of canister loading/switching mechanism

A sediment corer is a hollow tube that collects and extracts mud/soil/sediment and preserves it in that form/layering. In this case, I need to keep all the sediment, but don’t care if it gets mixed up
How deep and how compacted is the sediment?

My first thought is to take a metal cap that you can grind to have a serrated lip and fit a PVC pipe in one end. Im envisioning PVC pipes with a flap at one end that opens into the pipe. Now fit the pipe into the metal cap and have a matching cap on the other end with handles. Now use the apparatus to dig into the soil - as you push into the dirt it will open the flap and allow the soil in. As you retract it the pressure from the sediment escaping should force the flap shut.
You can keep replacing the PVC pipes for each drill attempt (or empty the one and reuse it, etc.)
You can drill holes in one end of each pipe (below the flap line and closer to the edge) with a pair of pegs to told the pipe in the cap.
